##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## He's not a robot. And we took enough from him without taking his free will, such as it is.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## Do you want to borrow my handkerchief, Dr. Toth?

//<Silence on recording.>//

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## The conscript's decision was sound, however inconvenient for us. I might have made the same choice myself--

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Except that it puts you in physical danger.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## Quite.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Although the timing //is// suspicious.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## How do you mean?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Covering your tracks, doctor?

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## What's she talking about?

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## I have no idea.

//<Security Chief Souther interrupts via radio.>//

##FFD300|**Chief Souther:**## Sir.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## G--

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## Go ahead.

##FFD300|**Chief Souther:**## Damage control is in high gear, but prevention is almost impossible. I've got people smashing screens throughout every level, but there's a lot of eyes and electronics in this hole. We need to get ahead of it at the source.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Thank you, Chief. As I said, we need to consider what Crius suggested.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Which was what?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Reformatting the network.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## No. I'm not going to sacrifice months of work just to give some lazy grunts a vacation from their jobs. The harm to our sustained program of research would be incalculable. Knock-on effects, opportunity loss...

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Don't you have backups?

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## As you know from the information security policies you yourself signed into force, sir, no. Our work is far too sensitive to expose it to outside scrutiny. Anything not migrated into the Deepwell -- and that's most everything -- would be lost if we reformatted.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## And you'd probably stoop to strangling us to prevent that from happening. 

//<Dr. Carlisle opens his mouth to respond.>//

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## No, don't comment, you don't need to. Just come up with a feasible plan B.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## No.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Right. Good. You understand.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## I do not understand.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## Plan B will be whatever //Crius// comes up with.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## But Crius isn't here!

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## You weren't wrong when you said Area-12's information security is one of its priorities. Once it is convinced the Deepwell is secure, it will attempt to solve the problem for us. No doubt it's monitoring remotely, through a thousand firewalls and proxies to keep itself clean.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Are you seriously saying you want to sit here and //wait// on the off chance that Crius eventually gets around to our survival on his priority list?!

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Yes.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## You're geniuses! Renaissance... people! Surely you can use the time to implement, I don't know, stopgaps!

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## No.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## Absolutely not. Crius is a //simulated// genius with a simulated brain immeasurably larger and more powerful than the human norm, with unrivaled access to a storehouse of data we can't get at, and the processing power to conduct effective //years// of hypothesizing every minute. Its biggest impediment is that it only knows the Area-12 situation up to the moment where it disconnected the Deepwell.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## So any plans we put into motion with our imperfect data and lack of time to iterate would only introduce a new variable Crius can't know about.

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## Therefore we can only make such interventions that it could be reasonably expected to expect from us. We need to get inside its head. Luckily, its two prime architects are in this room right now.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## But what if Crius decides not to come back at all?

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## That is certainly a consideration.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## No, it really isn't. This may be hard for you to comprehend, doctor, but our unfeeling friend is not motivated solely by self-interest.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## But you just said it! He doesn't //feel// anything. You can call him a friend, but he has no loyalty outside of his programming. That big brain you're relying on isn't organic like the Deepwell.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## That's not entirely--

##FF6D00|**Dr. Carlisle:**## We can't get into that now. We need to put our heads together. Don't curl your lip at me, //Quentin.// We've collaborated so effectually in the past.
