[[div class="blockquote"]]
##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## I think I know how we can slow it down.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## I thought you were trying to figure out Crius' plan.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## I was, but then I realized that's the wrong tack to take. Crius knows I'm here, and he... trusts me. He's certainly factored my presence into his analysis. He'll be expecting me to guess the first stage of his recovery plan, but I can't go farther than that! Because the whole plan will take into account the fact that I'll figure out the starting steps, and take them before he reconnects.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Are you sure you're not overthinking this?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Crius knows me almost as well as I know him, and I know him a lot better than he knows himself. He expects me to overthink it. I'm absolutely certain that by the time he's worked out all the variables, I need to have worked out the first one on my own.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## And what's the first variable? Hold on, shouldn't we wait for Hugo to get back?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Crius knows Carlisle too. The guy is hiding in one of his boltholes by now.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## What? He just stepped into the washroom!

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Sure he did.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Wait, //one// of his boltholes?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Please listen to me. sir. I think I know how this thing is moving around the facility.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Do //you// have a bolthole?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## I could find a few if I needed to. And so can this being. There are screens everywhere in Area-12, so why does it prioritize one route over another?

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## It's a dumb animal. Malicious panda code. Whatever.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## You think it's related to the 2528-C instances?

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## What? I don't know. I just heard you talking about the Deepwell.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Huh. Interesting. If that's the case... if we assume it's some sort of gestalt version of the bamboo ghosts, then it's survived the destruction of multiple entire universes. It's an apex survivor. It became code because becoming code was the best way to persist, but now it's locked into a much more logical manner of behaviour. It's a slave to its nature. So.... it's prioritizing screens which already feature specific key elements of its infosignature. Obviously. Why wouldn't it?

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Its what?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Its DNA. It's trying to propagate to a location where the displays are already primed to receive it, so it has the maximum number of possible retreat points. The dash-C entities survived by consuming conceptual data, using it to strengthen themselves, filling the holes in their essence after travelling light from universe to universe. That tracks with the way this thing is moving through the Area. Yeah. It's maximizing its survival potential.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## So we need to stop it from doing that.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## No. We need to harness that instinct, and use it to corral the thing somewhere we can seal it in. Create a perfect habitat.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## Like a zoo.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Right. If my guess is correct, Crius is monitoring to see if this happens, and will implement the remainder of his containment procedures when it does.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## And if he's not?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Then we'll have bought some time to solve this ourselves.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## So what's your game plan?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## I'm going to run all the security footage through a light scrambler to avoid making us the prime target, and I'm going to attempt to reconstruct its infosignature from the heavily artifacted data. Then we can reconfigure the screens leading up to the screening rooms in the ed center, where the visual fidelity control is finest, to subtly lure the anomaly in there.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## You're going to stare at still frames and figure out an AI's code from them?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## I didn't say it was an easy plan. I'm still on the clock.

##8060D2|**Director Forde:**## What do you need from me?

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Your security clearance code, twenty minutes, and complete silence.
